    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-05-14T12:42:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-05-13T16:00:00-05:00" n="296"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d296">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.48/1533: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hayes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates"
                            calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1943-05-14T13:42:00-04:00"
                            notBefore="1943-05-13T23:00:00+02:00">undated</date>.<lb/>[Received May
                        14, 1943—1:42 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1268. The following telegram has been sent to Algiers.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>14. May 13, midnight. For Murphy. Your 834, May 9, 4 p.m. to Department. Full
                        amount of $500,000 requested by French here and referred to in my 107, April
                        30, 7 p.m., is needed for refugee relief and it is desired by them that
                        funds granted for support of loyal French institutions in Spain be in
                        addition to this.</p>
                    <p>With regard to merits of request for funds for latter purpose I consider it
                        important that North African representation be in position to carry on
                        support of these institutions which occupy significant place in life of
                        French community in Spain and which are important centers for education and
                        dissemination of French culture. Otherwise it will be most difficult to keep
                        them out of hands of Vichy Government who strongly desire to retain
                        control.</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hayes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
